{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "b83d7aa8-e9b4-4bb6-9340-e8b4d6869dec",
    "name": "Auth System Api",
    "description": "The **Auth System API** is a secure, scalable, and centralized identity management service. It is designed to handle user authentication, authorization, and account security management. Built with a focus on protection and reliability, it ensures that only verified users can access sensitive resources within the system.\n\n### **🌐 Base URL Configuration**\n\nAll API requests must be prefixed with the following **Base URL**. Any endpoint mentioned in this documentation is a sub-path of this main address:\n\n**Development:** `https://localhost:xxxx`\n\n**Production:** `https://api.yourdomain.com`\n\n**Note:** Every endpoint listed in the following sections must be appended to the Base URL. For example:\n\n`Base URL` + `/api/auth/login`",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "50243565",
    "_collection_link": "https://go.postman.co/collection/50243565-b83d7aa8-e9b4-4bb6-9340-e8b4d6869dec?source=collection_link"
  },
